text:
Hollis Ave., east side, between Ninety-ninth Ave. (left, not shown) and One Hundredth Ave., showing in a set of two views the D. Ketchum residence located on a triangular plot of ground bounded in addition to the aforementioned streets by 193rd Street. It is now known as the Hollis Nurseries. From 1860 to 1891 the first mentioned person was the owner of this property. View No. 2 is taken from Ninety Fourth Ave., viewing S.W.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Hollis Ave., east side, between Ninety-ninth and One Hundredth Aves., showing the David Ketcham house of 1891. One GIlkinson maintained a florist establishment here in 1918.

April 1925.

folder: Hollis Avenue & Farmers Boulevard, Queens, NY
text:
Hollis Ave. (Old Country Road), south side, west of Farmers Boulevard, showing the S. Spragg house of 1860 which was demolished in 1925. District School No. 2 is at the left. All that is seen of it is the entrance into the building.

1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
